-circles.\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Sequenced Plastomes\n![[Species]]\n!Variety\n!Size ([[base pair|bp]])\n![[Gene]]s\n!Reference\n!Notes\n|-\n|''[[Chromera velia]]''\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|''[[Chroomonas]] mesostigmatica''\n|CCMP1168\n|139,403\n|189\n|<ref name=\"Kim2017\">{{cite journal | vauthors = Kim JI, Moore CE, Archibald JM, Bhattacharya D, Yi G, Yoon HS, Shin W | title = Evolutionary Dynamics of Cryptophyte Plastid Genomes | journal = Genome Biology and Evolution | volume = 9 | issue = 7 | pages = 1859\u20131872 | date = July 2017 | pmid = 28854597 | pmc = 5534331 | doi = 10.1093/gbe/evx123 }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|''[[Chroomonas]] placoidea''\n|CCAP978/8\n|139,432\n|186\n|<ref name=\"Kim2017\" />\n|Contains 3 annotated pseudogenes\n|-\n|''[[Cryptomonas]] curvata''\n|CNUKR\n|128,285\n|182\n|<ref name=\"Kim2017\" />\n|\n|-\n|''[[Cryptomonas]] paramecium''\n|CCAP977/2a\n|77,717\n|115\n|<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Donaher N, Tanifuji G, Onodera NT, Malfatti SA, Chain PS, Hara Y, Archibald JM | title = The complete plastid genome sequence of the secondarily nonphotosynthetic alga Cryptomonas paramecium: reduction, compaction, and accelerated evolutionary rate | journal = Genome Biology and Evolution | volume = 1 | pages = 439\u201348 | date = November 2009 | pmid = 20333213 | pmc = 2839278 | doi = 10.1093/gbe/evp047 }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|[[Emiliania huxleyi]]\n|CCMP 373\n|105,309\n|154\n|<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = S\u00e1nchez Puerta MV, Bachvaroff TR, Delwiche CF | title = The complete plastid genome sequence of the haptophyte Emiliania huxleyi: a comparison to other plastid genomes | journal = DNA Research | volume = 12 | issue = 2 | pages = 151\u20136 | date = 2005-01-01 | pmid = 16303746 | doi = 10.1093/dnares/12.2.151 | doi-access = free }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|''[[Guillardia]] [[Guillardia theta|theta]]''\n|\n|121,524\n|167\n|<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Douglas SE, Penny SL | title = The plastid genome of the cryptophyte alga, Guillardia theta: c