ete plastid genomes is maintained by the [[National Center for Biotechnology Information|NCBI]] in a public repository.<ref>{{Cite web|url=ftp://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/refseq/release/plastid/|title=Index of /refseq/release/plastid|website=ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov|access-date=2017-01-08}}</ref>\n\n==Plants==\n===Bryophytes ''s.l.''===\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Sequenced Plastomes\n![[Species]]\n!Variety\n!Size ([[base pair|bp]])\n![[Gene]]s\n!Reference\n!Notes\n|-\n|''[[Aneura (plant)|Aneura]] [[Aneura mirabilis|mirabilis]]''\n|\n|108,007\n|\n|<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Wickett NJ, Zhang Y, Hansen SK, Roper JM, Kuehl JV, Plock SA, Wolf PG, DePamphilis CW, Boore JL, Goffinet B | title = Functional gene losses occur with minimal size reduction in the plastid genome of the parasitic liverwort Aneura mirabilis | journal = Molecular Biology and Evolution | volume = 25 | issue = 2 | pages = 393\u2013401 | date = February 2008 | pmid = 18056074 | doi = 10.1093/molbev/msm267 | url = http://mbe.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/msm267v1 | doi-access = free }}</ref><ref>[https://search.proquest.com/docview/304864708 Plastid genome evolution of the non-photosynthetic liverwort Aneura mirabilis (Malmb.) Wickett & Goffinet (Aneuraceae)]</ref>\n|parasitic liverwort; plastome contains many pseudogenes\n|-\n|''[[Anthoceros]] [[Anthoceros formosae|formosae]]''\n|\n|161,162 \n|122\n|<ref>{{cite journal | vauthors = Kugita M, Kaneko A, Yamamoto Y, Takeya Y, Matsumoto T, Yoshinaga K | title = The complete nucleotide sequence of the hornwort (Anthoceros formosae) chloroplast genome: insight into the earliest land plants | journal = Nucleic Acids Research | volume = 31 | issue = 2 | pages = 716\u201321 | date = January 2003 | pmid = 12527781 | pmc = 140519 | doi = 10.1093/nar/gkg155 | url = http://nar.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/abstract/31/2/716 }}</ref>\n|hornwort; extensive RNA editing of plastome\n|-\n|''[[Marchantia]] [[Marchantia polymorpha|polymorpha]]''\n|\n|121