12/04/lista-completa-de-ganadores-kids-choice-awards-2012/ |archivedate=October 12, 2013 }}</ref>\n|-\n| 2013\n| Australian Kids' Choice Awards\n| [[Nickelodeon Australian Kids' Choice Awards#Nickelodeon Slimefest 2013|Aussie's Fave Nick Star]]\n| Herself\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://kca.nickelodeon.com.au/vote#category:Aussie's_Fave_Nick_Star |title=Aussie's Fave Nick Star |work=Nickelodeon |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6Nf1mnR1V?url=http://kca.nickelodeon.com.au/vote |archivedate=February 25, 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\n| Kids' Choice Awards\n| [[2014 Kids' Choice Awards#Favorite TV Actress|Favorite TV Actress]]\n| ''[[Sam & Cat]]''\n| {{nom}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/kids-choice-awards-2014-nominees-681858|title=Favorite TV Actress|work=Nickelodeon | first=Philiana|last=Ng}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Jennette McCurdy}}\n* {{Official website}}\n* {{IMDb name|1390614}}\n* {{AllMusic|class=artist|id=jennette-mccurdy-mn0001717011}}\n* {{Discogs artist|Jennette McCurdy}}\n* {{AllMovie name|376128}}\n* {{Tcmdb name}}\n* {{Twitter}}\n* [https://youtube.com/channel/UC8nuJ5ZrPFl_b93zT2iHD9g Jennette McCurdy] on [[YouTube]]\n\n{{Jennette McCurdy}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McCurdy, Jennette}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century American women singers]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Long Beach, California]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Orange County, California]]\n[[Category:Actresses of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:American child singers]]\n[[Category:American columnists]]\n[[Category:American female country singers]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American people of Dutch descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of French descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Swedish descent]]\n[[Category:American pop singers]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American voice actresses]]\n[[Category:American web producers]]\n[[Category:American women non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:Capitol Records artists]]\n[[Category:Child pop musicians]]\n[[Category:Country musicians from California]]\n[[Category:Journalists from California]]\n[[Category:Musicians from Long Beach, California]]\n[[Category:People from Garden Grove, California]]\n[[Category:People from Studio City, Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Screenwriters from California]]\n[[Category:Women columnists]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-pc1}}\n{{short description|American actress, producer, screenwriter, and singer}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name            = Jennette McCurdy\n|image           = Jennette McCurdy 2012.jpg\n|caption         = McCurdy at the 2012 [[Hall of Game Awards]]\n|birth_name      = Jennette Michelle Faye McCurdy\n|birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1992|6|26|mf=yes}}\n|birth_place     = [[Long Beach, California]], U.S.\n|residence       = [[Studio City, California]], U.S.\n|years_active    = 2000\u2013present\n|occupation      = {{hlist|Actress|singer|writer|producer|director}}\n|module          = {{Infobox musical artist|embed = yes\n|background      = solo_singer\n|genre           = {{hlist|[[Country music|Country]]|[[country pop]]}}\n|instrument      = {{hlist|Vocals|guitar|keyboard<ref>{{YouTube|T__MW92c3R0|Be You}}</ref>}}\n|label           = {{hlist|[[Capitol Records Nashville|Capitol Nashville]]|[[EMI]]}}\n|associated_acts =\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.jennettemccurdy.com}}\n}}}}\n'''Jennette Michelle Faye McCurdy''' (born June 26, 1992) is an American actress, YouTuber, singer, director, and writer.<ref>{{cite web|title=iCARLY's Jennette McCurdy Covers @RUNWAY Winter 2014 Issue|url=http://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/iCARLYs-Jennette-McCurdy-Covers-RUNWAY-Winter-2014-Issue-20140107|website=Broadway World|accessdate=March 14, 2015}}</ref> She is known for playing [[Sam Puckett (iCarly)|Sam Puckett]] on the [[Nickelodeon]] sitcom ''[[iCarly]]'' and its [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] series ''[[Sam & Cat]]''. McCurdy has also appeared in a number of television series, including ''[[Victorious]]'', ''[[Zoey 101]]'', ''[[True Jackson VP]]'', ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]'', and ''[[Lincoln Heights (TV series)|Lincoln Heights]]'', and has also produced, written, and starred in her own online series titled ''[[What's Next for Sarah?]]'' From May 2015 to August 2016, she starred in the [[Netflix]]/[[Citytv]] drama series ''[[Between (TV series)|Between]]'' as Wiley Day.\n\n==Early life==\nJennette Michelle Faye McCurdy was born on June 26, 1992 in [[Long Beach, California]], and grew up in nearby [[Garden Grove, California|Garden Grove]].<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web|last=Nastos|first=Michael G.|title=Jennette McCurdy|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/jennette-mccurdy-mn0001717011/biography|publisher=Allmusic|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Studio City\">{{cite web|url=https://www.zillow.com/blog/nickelodeons-jennette-mccurdy-buys-in-studio-city-126130/|title=Nickelodeon's Jennette McCurdy Buys in Studio City|last=Sherman|first=Catherine|publisher=Zillow|date=July 5, 2013|accessdate=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===2000\u20132006: Career beginning===\nMcCurdy started her acting career in 2000 at the age of eight on ''[[MADtv]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=TV Roles |url=http://www.jennettemccurdy.com/tvroles.html |work=Jennette McCurdy's Official Website |accessdate=September 4, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110901222506/http://www.jennettemccurdy.com/tvroles.html |archivedate=September 1, 2011 }}</ref> Since then she appeared in television series, including ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'', ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]'', ''[[Lincoln Heights (TV series)|Lincoln Heights]]'', ''[[Will & Grace]]'', ''[[The Penguins of Madagascar]]'', ''[[Zoey 101]]'', ''[[True Jackson, VP]]'', ''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit|Law and Order SVU]]'', ''[[Medium (TV series)|Medium]]'', ''[[Judging Amy]]'', ''[[The Inside (TV series)|The Inside]]'', ''[[Karen Sisco]]'', ''[[Over There]]'', and ''[[Close to Home (2005 TV series)|Close to Home]]''. In 2003, she had the chance to act with her inspiration, [[Harrison Ford]], in the film ''[[Hollywood Homicide]]''. In 2005, she was nominated for a [[Young Artist Award]] for Best Performance in a Television Series \u2013 Guest Starring Young Actress for her performance in ''[[Strong Medicine]]'' as Hailey Campos. She has also appeared in several commercials, such as one for Sprint and a [[public service announcement]] on crossing the road safely.\n\n===2007\u20132012: ''iCarly'' and music===\n[[File:Jennette McCurdy at the Kids' Choice Awards.jpg|thumb|left|McCurdy at the [[2010 Kids' Choice Awards]]]]\nIn 2007, she won a starring role in the Nickelodeon TV series ''[[iCarly]]'' as [[Sam Puckett (iCarly)|Sam Puckett]], a series she would be a part of until its end in 2012. In 2008, she was nominated for a Young Artist Award for her work on ''iCarly'' and her performance as Dory Sorenson in the TV movie ''[[The Last Day of Summer (2007 film)|The Last Day of Summer]]''. She was nominated for a [[Teen Choice Awards|2009 Teen Choice Award]] in the Favorite TV Sidekick category for her work on ''iCarly''. She played Bertha in ''[[Fred: The Movie]]'', a movie based on a [[YouTube]] series about [[Fred Figglehorn]].\n\nIn June 2008, McCurdy announced on her official website that she was working on her debut album. The first single, \"So Close\", was released on March 10, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jennettemccurdy.com/news.html?item=9 |title=First Single \"Not That Far Away\" From Upcoming Debut Album |publisher=Jennettemccurdy.com |accessdate=November 7, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111107020853/http://www.jennettemccurdy.com/news.html?item=9 |archivedate=November 7, 2011 }}</ref> On May 19 her cover of the [[Amanda Stott]] song \"Homeless Heart\" was released.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Amanda-Stott-Chasing-The-Sky/release/1751959|title=Amanda Stott - Chasing The Sky|website=Discogs|language=en|access-date=June 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=316244960&id=316244934|title=Homeless Heart \u2013 Single by Jennette McCurdy \u2013 Download Homeless Heart \u2013 Single on iTunes |publisher=itunes.apple.com |date=May 19, 2009 |accessdate=May 19, 2010}}</ref> The song was released in honor of McCurdy's recently deceased friend Cody Waters, who died at the age of nine from [[brain cancer]], and 20% of the proceeds were donated to the Cody Waters Foundation.<ref name=\"single\">{{cite web|last=McCurdy |first=Jennette |title=New single |work=Jennette McCurdy's Official Website |date=May 4, 2009 |url=http://jennettemccurdy.com/all-about-me/new-single/ |accessdate=May 8, 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090509171147/http://jennettemccurdy.com/all-about-me/new-single/ |archivedate=May 9, 2009 }}</ref> She met Waters through [[St.&nbsp;Jude Children's Research Hospital]]. In mid-2009, McCurdy signed with country music label [[Capitol Records Nashville]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cmt.com/news/news-in-brief/1615535/jennette-mccurdy-of-nickelodeons-icarly-signs-with-capitol-nashville.jhtml|title=Jennette McCurdy of Nickelodeon's iCarly Signs With Capitol Nashville|publisher=[[Country Music Television]]|date=July 8, 2009|accessdate=January 18, 2012}}</ref> On April 16, 2010, samples of select songs from McCurdy's upcoming debut country album were released online. The song clips were released in order for fans to vote for which one they believed should be McCurdy's first single.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theboot.com/2010/04/16/jennette-mccurdy-songs/ |title=Jennette McCurdy Lets Fans Help Decide Debut Single |publisher=The Boot |date=April 16, 2010 |accessdate=May 19, 2010}}</ref> \"[[Not That Far Away]]\" received the most votes, and was released to country radio on May 24, 2010 and [[iTunes]] on June 1.\n[[File:Jennette McCurdy (6219737643).jpg|thumb|McCurdy at Australian Kids' Choice Awards 2011]]\n\nShe released an [[extended play|EP]] on August 17, 2010, which included \"Not That Far Away\" and three new songs: \"Stronger\", \"Put Your Arms Around Someone\", and \"Break Your Heart\". The [[iTunes]] version included \"Me with You\" as a bonus track. McCurdy's second single, \"[[Generation Love]]\", was released as a digital download on March 22, 2011,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jennettemccurdy.com/news.html?item=26 |title=\"Generation Love\" is Now Available! |publisher=Jennettemccurdy.com |date=March 22, 2011 |accessdate=November 7, 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111107020821/http://www.jennettemccurdy.com/news.html?item=26 |archivedate=November 7, 2011}}</ref> followed by its release to radio April 25, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.allaccess.com/country/future-releases|title=Future Releases for Country Radio Stations|publisher=All Access |accessdate=May 30, 2011}}</ref> Capitol Nashville released McCurdy's self-named seven-track EP on February 8, 2012<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jennettemccurdy.com/news.html?item=48 |title=Jennette McCurdy |publisher=Jennette McCurdy |accessdate=March 5, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120425040357/http://www.jennettemccurdy.com/news.html?item=48 |archivedate=April 25, 2012 }}</ref> at clothing retailer [[Tween Brands|Justice]].<ref name=new2012>{{cite news|url=http://jennettemccurdy.com/news.html?item=43 |title=New Music In Justice Stores Tuesday, January 24! |work=Jennette McCurdy official website |date=January 18, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120123233829/http://jennettemccurdy.com/news.html?item=43 |archivedate=January 23, 2012}}</ref> The full-length, ten-track edition was released to iTunes on June 5, 2012 and is her first full-length album. On July 11, 2012, ''Fanlala'' released an interview with McCurdy in which she confirmed that she has since left Capitol Records Nashville, saying, \"I'm kind of between projects right now. I actually just left Capitol Records recently. I'm really just deciding what else I want to do next. Right now I'm working on my new show, and I'm just figuring out where I should take my music from here.\"<ref>[http://www.fanlala.com/news/exclusive-interview-jennette-mccurdy-0 Exclusive interview on] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121109055052/http://www.fanlala.com/news/exclusive-interview-jennette-mccurdy-0 |date=November 9, 2012 }}. Fanlala.com. Retrieved December 18, 2012.</ref> On July 31, 2012, ''How to Rock'' released an interview with McCurdy, in which she talked about her acting and music careers.<ref>[http://learnhowtorock.alloyentertainment.com/icarlys-jennette-mccurdy-talks-about-acting-and-music/ Interview on] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130125111954/http://learnhowtorock.alloyentertainment.com/icarlys-jennette-mccurdy-talks-about-acting-and-music/ |date=January 25, 2013 }}. Learnhowtorock.alloyentertainment.com (December 12, 2012). Retrieved December 18, 2012.</ref> A follow-up interview was released on August 8, in which McCurdy reflects on her music career.<ref>[http://learnhowtorock.alloyentertainment.com/jennette-mccurdy-music-career/ Janette McCurdy on How to be a Rock Star]{{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131012040019/http://learnhowtorock.alloyentertainment.com/jennette-mccurdy-music-career/ |date=October 12, 2013 }}. Learnhowtorock.alloyentertainment.com (December 11, 2012). Retrieved December 18, 2012.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/jennette-mccurdy/id530820687 |title=Jennette McCurdy On iTunes |publisher=itunes.apple.com |year=2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140819105458/https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/jennette-mccurdy/id530820687 |archivedate=August 19, 2014 }}</ref>\n\n===2013\u20132015: ''Sam & Cat''===\nMcCurdy starred alongside [[Ariana Grande]] in the Nickelodeon series ''[[Sam & Cat]]'', reprising her role as Sam Puckett, with Grande reprising her role as [[Cat Valentine (Sam & Cat)|Cat Valentine]]. The series' plot centers on the girls becoming roommates and starting their own babysitting business. It premiered on June 8, 2013. In 2014 McCurdy along with good friend and former co-star [[Miranda Cosgrove]] were absent from the [[2014 Kids' Choice Awards|Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]]. Explaining her absence, McCurdy stated that Nickelodeon put her in an \"uncomfortable, compromising, unfair situation\" where she had to look out for herself, and McCurdy and Grande were having problems with the network over their respective salaries, and that McCurdy accused Nickelodeon of paying Grande more money.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodtake.com/ariana-grande-vs-jennette-mccurdy-why-whats-next-sarah-video-gloriana-upset-arianators-53570|author=Siegel, Melissa|title=Ariana Grande vs. Jennette McCurdy! Why 'What's Next for Sarah' Video of Gloriana Upset Arianators After Rumored 'Sam & Cat' Feud|publisher=Hollywood Take|date=August 15, 2014|accessdate=August 17, 2014}}</ref> The network placed ''Sam & Cat'' into hiatus. The network initially stated that the hiatus was planned and that the series was not cancelled.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ew.com/article/2014/04/02/nickelodeon-sam-cat-cancellation-rumors|title=Nickelodeon denies 'Sam & Cat' cancellation rumors|work=Entertainment Weekly's EW.com | first=Ariana|last=Bacle|date=April 2, 2014}}</ref> On July 13, 2014, Nickelodeon announced that, after only one season, ''Sam & Cat'' was cancelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2014/07/sam-cat-wont-cancelled-nickelodeon-803466/|title=Nickelodeon cancels hit 'Sam & Cat' After One Season, On-Set Discord - Deadline |author=Nellie Andreeva|work=Deadline}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://grantland.com/hollywood-prospectus/know-your-beef-ariana-grande-vs-jennette-mccurdy-vs-andre-drummond/|title=Know Your Beef: Ariana Grande vs. Jennette McCurdy (vs. Andre Drummond)|author=Emily Yoshida|work=Grantland}}</ref><ref name=\"abcnews\">{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/video/jennette-mccurdy-28947183|title=One-on-One With Jennette McCurdy|author=ABC News|work=ABC News}}</ref> In an interview on ''Entertainment Pop'', McCurdy mentioned that she later made up with Grande.<ref name=\"abcnews\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2014/07/24/ariana-grande-grandfather-died-messages-of-support-death-twitter/|title=Ariana Grande's Grandpa Dies \u2014 Friends & Fans Console Her|publisher=Hollywood Life|date=July 24, 2014|accessdate=September 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\nOn August 13, 2014, McCurdy launched the online show ''[[What's Next for Sarah?]]''. She served as the star of the series as well as the writer of the show, along with duties as executive producer and editor. She says that the show is based loosely on her life and that the character she plays, Sarah Bronson, is based on her.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/jennettemccurdy/status/499673718180675584 |title=Jennette McCurdy on Twitter |work=Twitter |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150131173002/https://twitter.com/jennettemccurdy/status/499673718180675584 |archivedate=January 31, 2015 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/jennettemccurdy/status/499683041237667840 |title=Jennette McCurdy on Twitter |work=Twitter |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150201131138/https://twitter.com/jennettemccurdy/status/499683041237667840 |archivedate=February 1, 2015 }}</ref><ref name=\"whatsnextforsarah.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.whatsnextforsarah.com/|title=What's Next For Sarah?|work=What's Next For Sarah?}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/jennettemccurdy/comments/2dgdqg/jennette_mccurdy_aka_curmudgeon457_here_ama/|title=Jennette McCurdy (a.k.a. curmudgeon457) here, AMA! : jennettemccurdy|work=reddit}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, she began starring in the [[Netflix]] drama series ''[[Between (TV series)|Between]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2014/10/jennette-mccurdy-between-drama-series-netflix-city-855286/|title=Jennette McCurdy Cast In Thriller Drama Series For Netflix - Deadline|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|date=October 20, 2014|access-date=October 20, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.yahoo.com/blogs/tv-news/jennette-mccurdy-between-netflix-on-location-toronto-214618059.html|title=Touring Toronto: On Location With 'Between' Star Jennette McCurdy|website=[[Yahoo TV]]|last=Evans|first=Andrew|date=January 24, 2015|access-date=}}</ref> It was also announced that she would star in teen comedy ''[[Little Bitches]]'' alongside [[Virginia Gardner]] and [[Kiersey Clemons]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jennette McCurdy, Virginia Gardner Join Teen Comedy Little Bitches|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/jennette-mccurdy-virginia-gardner-little-bitches-1201661873/|website=Variety|accessdate=December 15, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016\u2013present: Current work ===\nIn August 2016, McCurdy signed a deal to develop projects with digital production company Canvas Media Studios to further utilize her social media connections with fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jennette-mccurdy-develop-scripted-projects-920557 |title=Jennette McCurdy to Develop Scripted Projects With Digital Studio Canvas Media (Exclusive) |publisher=Hollywood Reporter |date=August 18, 2016 |accessdate=March 9, 2017}}</ref> She also starred as Claire in the psychological thriller film ''[[Pet (film)|Pet]]''.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/jennette-mccurdy-indie-pet-1201547474/ |title=Jennette McCurdy to Co-Star in Indie 'Pet'|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |last=Kroll|first=Justin|date=August 11, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSince 2016, ''Between'' was not renewed for a third season and while critics acknowledged McCurdy as \u2033one of the few cast members who can act\u2033<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/tv/la-et-st-young-adult-between-review-20150516-column.html|title=Review There's no growing old in the YA thriller 'Between'|last=McNamara|first=Mary|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=May 21, 2015|accessdate=August 11, 2015}}</ref>, she expressed on her website that she felt ashamed of 90% of her resume.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McCurdy |first1=Jennette |title=Bio - jennettemccurdy.com |url=https://www.jennettemccurdy.com/bio/ |accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref> She eventually decided to quit acting and to pursuit writing and directing in 2017<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/jennette-mccurdy-makes-directorial-debut-short-film-1152455|title=Jennette McCurdy Makes Directorial Debut With Short Film|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=October 26, 2018|language=en}}</ref>: \n\n{{Quote\n |text=\"I never got the chance to be cast in a project I was proud to be part of. Now I have a better chance of making things I\u2019m proud of than getting cast in things I\u2019m proud of.\"\n |author=Jennette McCurdy\n |source=The Hollywood Reporter, 15 October 2018}}\n\nOnce a very active user of Twitter, Facebook, Snapchat and Instagram, she also deleted all her posts on social media from the past and had set all her past videos and [[Vlog|vlogs]] \u2033private\u2033 on YouTube and [[Vimeo]].\n\nIn 2018, McCurdy made her debut as a film director with a short film titled ''Kenny.''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.shortoftheweek.com/2018/10/15/kenny|title=Kenny by Jennette McCurdy {{!}} Dramedy Short Film|website=Short of the Week|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> The [[Comedy-drama|dramedy]] film, both written and directed by her, was inspired by the death of her mother and features an all-female crew. ''Kenny'' was featured in ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' and on Short of the Week. She has since released three short films she wrote and directed: ''The Grave'', ''The McCurdys,'' a semi-autobiographical short based on her childhood<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.jennettemccurdy.com/projects/|title=Projects|website=Jennette Mccurdy|language=en-US|access-date=December 23, 2018}}</ref> and ''Strong Independent Women,'' a short that deals with eating disorders.<ref>{{Citation|last=Jennette McCurdy|title=an eating disorder short film: Strong Independent Women|date=March 3, 2019|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9qJoiz7lua0|access-date=March 8, 2019}}</ref> In late 2018, she announced that she hopes to direct more films.<ref>{{Citation|last=Jennette McCurdy|title=a little announcement...|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7lMDSFaGvfI|access-date=December 28, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, she starred in her one-woman [[Tragicomedy|tragicomedy]] show \u2033I'm Glad My Mom Died\u2033 in various theaters in Los Angeles and New York. She had to set her show into hiatus after the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]] reached United States territory. For the first time since she opened up publicly about her [[eating disorder]] in 2019, she posted a new video on YouTube where she sings about her personal implications by finding herself in quarantine due to the outbreak.<ref>{{cite web |last1=McCurdy |first1=Jennette |title=the corona song |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6xiiN5SLP0Y |accessdate=16 April 2020 |date=23 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Writing==\nIn 2011, McCurdy began writing a series of articles for ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]''. She has written a total of eight pieces for the paper, on topics ranging from [[Shirley Temple]]<ref>{{cite news|author=|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2014/02/12/nickelodeons-jennette-mccurdy-on-why-america-drank-up-shirley-temple/|title=Nickelodeon's Jennette McCurdy on Why America Drank Up Shirley Temple - Speakeasy - WSJ |publisher=Blogs.wsj.com |date=February 12, 2014 |accessdate=April 18, 2014}}</ref> to body shaming and a corporate culture which she perceives as [[smoke and mirrors]].<ref>{{cite news|author=|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2014/01/22/do-i-look-fat-in-this-article-jennette-mccurdy-on-beauty-and-body-shaming/ |title=Do I Look Fat in This Article? Jennette McCurdy on Beauty and Body Shaming - Speakeasy - WSJ |publisher=Blogs.wsj.com |date=January 22, 2014 |accessdate=April 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\nShe is also a columnist for ''[[Seventeen (American magazine)|Seventeen]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web|last=McCurdy |first=Jennette |url=http://www.seventeen.com/archives/entertainment/reviews/by_author/108132/3;1 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140407042827/http://www.seventeen.com/archives/entertainment/reviews/by_author/108132/3;1 |url-status=dead |archive-date=April 7, 2014 |title=TV Music and Movie Reviews for Teens |work=Seventeen |accessdate=April 18, 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.fanlala.com/news/jennette-mccurdy-blogging-seventeen |title=Jennette McCurdy is Blogging for Seventeen! |publisher=Fanlala.com |date=January 8, 2014 |accessdate=April 18, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140408212531/http://www.fanlala.com/news/jennette-mccurdy-blogging-seventeen |archive-date=April 8, 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> She has also written for ''[[The Huffington Post]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/jennette-mccurdy/|title=Jennette McCurdy |work=huffingtonpost.com}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 2013, McCurdy moved to [[Studio City, Los Angeles|Studio City, California]].<ref name=\"Studio City\"/>\n\nMcCurdy composed an article titled \"Off-Camera, My Mom's Fight With Cancer\", which was published in ''[[The Wall Street Journal]]'' in June 2011. It describes in detail her mother Debra's ongoing battle with cancer and how her family coped with the situation. The article also features advice from McCurdy on living with such a situation.<ref>{{cite news|title=Off-Camera, My Mom's Fight With Cancer|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/speakeasy/2011/06/11/off-camera-my-moms-fight-with-cancer/|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|accessdate=June 11, 2011|first=Jennette|last=McCurdy |date=June 11, 2011}}</ref> On September 20, 2013, her mother died after battling cancer for 17 years.<ref>{{cite web |title=Jennette McCurdy's Mother Passes Away After Battling Cancer |url=http://www.eonline.com/news/461479/jennette-mccurdy-s-mother-passes-away-after-battling-cancer |publisher=E! |date=September 20, 2013 |accessdate=September 22, 2013}}</ref>\n\nOn March 8, 2019, McCurdy revealed her battle with [[anorexia]] and later [[bulimia]] beginning at age 11 in an article in the ''[[Huffington Post]]'' describing in detail how it started over a need to look smaller and thinner for younger roles, her mother's and the entertainment industry's aiding of the disordered eating, seeking help after her sister-in-law noticed the disorder while McCurdy was in [[Toronto]] filming ''Between'', and various \"come-to-Jesus moments\" such as once losing a tooth from regurgitating stomach fluids that wore down her [[tooth enamel]] and passing out on a friend's bathroom floor from dehydration.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffpost.com/entry/jennette-mccurdy-eating-disorder_n_5c812d61e4b0e62f69ea8363|title=Former Nickelodeon Star Jennette McCurdy Opens Up About Her Eating Disorder|last=McCurdy|first=Jennette|date=March 8, 2019|website=HuffPost|language=en|access-date=March 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\